<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<ibexconfig>
	<!--
		Configuration file for Ibex (http://www.xmlpdf.com/) 
		Used in IBEXFOPProcessorService.
		 
		This file should be available in the root of the classpath for 
		Ibex to pick.
		
		Otherwise, a different location can be set by launching the JVM 
		with: -Dibexconfig=/usr/ibex/ibexconfig.xml
		
		The font definitions below must match Unicode fonts available in 
		the system if we want to display double byte languages, such as 
		Arabic or Chinese.

		Notice that there are no known fonts that provide a complete 
		Unicode character set.

		A few options for Sans-serif in Windows:
		####################################################################
		Arial Unicode MS (Version 0.84 or later)
		Latin, Greek, Cyrillic, Hebrew, Arabic, Devanagari, Thai, CJK
		(Not include with Windows, included with Office 2000 and later)
		http://www.microsoft.com/typography/fonts/font.aspx?FMID=185
		
		Tahoma (version 2.30 and later)
		Latin, Greek, Cyrillic, Hebrew, Arabic, Thai 
		http://www.microsoft.com/typography/fonts/font.aspx?FMID=157
		
		Microsoft Sans Serif (Version 1.41 and later)
		Latin, Greek, Cyrillic, Hebrew, Arabic, Thai
		http://www.microsoft.com/typography/fonts/font.aspx?FMID=1130
		
		Segoe UI (Versio 1.0 or later)
		Latin, Greek, Cyrillic, Arabic 
		http://www.microsoft.com/typography/fonts/font.aspx?FMID=1310
		####################################################################
		
		Monospace - The only option in Windows for monospace with a reasonable 
		coverage for different scripts is Courier New:
		####################################################################
		Courier New (Version 0.84 or later)
		Latin, Greek, Cyrillic, Hebrew, Arabic, Thai
		http://www.microsoft.com/typography/fonts/font.aspx?FMID=193
		####################################################################
		
		Notice that we can have different fonts per language. The fonts for 
		PDF are defined in the core_xx.properties file.
		In the core_en.properties file we can find:
		PDF_LABEL_FONT = Helvetica
		PDF_DATA_FONT = Courier
		
		IMPORTANT: In this file font names must be lowercase!

	-->
	
	<!-- Sans serif font -->
	<font bold="false" file="c:/windows/fonts/arialuni.ttf" italic="false" name="helvetica"/>
	<font bold="true" file="c:/windows/fonts/arialuni.ttf" italic="false" name="helvetica"/>
	<font bold="false" file="c:/windows/fonts/arialuni.ttf" italic="true" name="helvetica"/>
	<font bold="true" file="c:/windows/fonts/arialuni.ttf" italic="true" name="helvetica"/>

	<!-- Monospace font -->
	<font bold="false" file="c:/windows/fonts/cour.ttf" italic="false" name="courier"/>
	<font bold="true" file="c:/windows/fonts/courbd.ttf" italic="false" name="courier"/>
	<font bold="false" file="c:/windows/fonts/couri.ttf" italic="true" name="courier"/>
	<font bold="true" file="c:/windows/fonts/courbi.ttf" italic="true" name="courier"/>

</ibexconfig>